# API Surface (Nitro / H3)

Handlers live under app/server/api/. Filenames end with .<method>.ts and use directory nesting for path segments.

Examples by area (not exhaustive):

- Auth and user
  - login.post.ts, logout.post.ts, change-password.post.ts, two-factor-auth.ts, verify-two-factor-auth.post.ts, disable-two-factor-auth.post.ts
  - mfa/*: email send/toggle/verify; passkey options/register/verify/delete; totp verify
  - user.get.ts, user.post.ts, user/notification-settings.patch.ts, validate-token.ts
- Accounts and membership
  - account/[accountId]/members.get.ts, members/[userId].delete.ts, members/[userId].patch.ts
  - account-invite.get.ts, account-invite.post.ts, account-invite/[id].delete.ts, account-invite/accept.post.ts, account-invite/validate.get.ts
- Budgets and categories
  - budget.post.ts, budget/[id].delete.ts, budget/[id].patch.ts, budget/[id]/reset.post.ts
  - categories.get.ts, category.post.ts, category.patch.ts, category.delete.ts
- Registers and entries
  - register.ts, register-entry.post.ts, .patch.ts, .delete.ts
  - register-entry-transfer.post.ts, register-entry-transfer-create.post.ts
  - register-entry-applied.post.ts, register-entry-skip.post.ts
  - account-register.post.ts, account-register.delete.ts, account-register-sort.post.ts
  - snapshot endpoints: snapshot.post.ts, snapshot/[id].get.ts, snapshot/[id].delete.ts, snapshots.get.ts, snapshot-register/[id].get.ts
- Reoccurrences and health
  - reoccurrence.post.ts, reoccurrence.delete.ts, reoccurrence-health.get.ts
  - register-entry-match-reoccurrence.post.ts
- Reports
  - reports/categories.get.ts
- Bills
  - bills.get.ts, bills/profile/[id].patch.ts, bill-instance/[id].patch.ts, bills/reminders/evaluate.post.ts
- Reconciliation
  - reconciliation/period*.get.ts/.post.ts, item/[entryId].patch.ts, period/[id]/close.post.ts
- Notifications
  - notifications.get.ts, notifications/count.get.ts, notifications/[id]/dismiss.patch.ts
- Integrations
  - plaid-link.post.ts, plaid-link.ts, plaid-list-accounts.ts, plaid-link-accounts.post.ts, plaid-disconnect-account.post.ts
  - plaid-synced-accounts.get.ts, register-entry/[id]/plaid.get.ts
  - webhook/plaid.post.ts
  - crypto: crypto-sync.post.ts, crypto-register-chains/[id].get.ts, crypto-tokens/[id].get.ts
  - asset-value-estimate.post.ts, vehicle-value-estimate.post.ts
- Forecast, tasks, and maintenance
  - recalculate.post.ts
  - tasks/* (backup, recalculate, sync-plaid, sync-plaid-balance, check-yearly-reoccurrences, cleanup-balance-entries, sync-google-sheet*.post.ts, etc.)
  - lists.ts (misc list endpoints), countries.get.ts, forecast-risk-alerts*.ts
- Admin
  - admin/*: accounts, users, audit-logs, integration-alerts, integration-job-logs, postmark/messages, openai-request-logs, system-status, plaid-sync-logs
  - admin microservice integration: microservice-reencrypt-migrate.post.ts, accounts/[id]/sync-plaid.post.ts, ...
- Health and nuxt
  - routes/_nuxt.get.ts (nuxt asset serving), routes/sitemap.xml.ts
  - routes/health/live.get.ts, routes/health/ready.get.ts

## Common handler patterns

- Use server/clients/prismaClient.ts to access DB
- Wrap with withErrorHandler/handleApiError to normalize errors
- Enforce authorization via middleware (server/middleware/auth.ts) and helpers (accountAccess.ts, requireAdmin.ts)
- Validate payloads with Zod (schema/zod.ts) where applicable
- For long operations, prefer enqueuing a BullMQ job (server/queues/*) and return a 202/OK acknowledgement

## Adding an endpoint safely

1. Create app/server/api/<feature>/<name>.<method>.ts
2. Parse/validate input (Zod from app/schema when relevant)
3. Use helpers for access checks; return consistent errors
4. Add unit/integration tests under app/server/api/__tests__ covering happy and error paths
5. If writes affect derived data (e.g., summaries), ensure queues or services update/cache/persist appropriately

## Client usage

- Composables: useAPI.ts or useAppFetch.ts are responsible for calling /api/* endpoints and handling auth/session
- Pinia stores (authStore, listStore) coordinate state and trigger API calls

